    <div class="q-and-a">
        <div class="row">
            <h3 class="headline centered">
                <span>Frequently asked questions</span>
            </h3>
            <div class="small-12 medium-4 columns">
                <div class="question-item">
                    <h5>How would you define a developer?</h5>
                    <p>
                        A developer is every person in your organization working directly with Handsontable source code.
                        That includes implementing, integrating or changing the code.
                    </p>
                    <h5>How many licenses do I need?</h5>
                    <p>You need one license for every developer working with Handsontable. Licenses are not assigned
                        to a particular person but to each seat.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="small-12 medium-4 columns">
                <div class="question-item">
                    <h5>Can I still use Handsontable after 12 months?</h5>
                    <p>Yes, you can. Once you buy a license you can use it without time boundaries.
                        Although after 12 months from the purchase date you lose the possibility to get
                        updates and support.</p>
                    <h5>Can I edit the source code?</h5>
                    <p>Yes, Handsontable license allows to use source code and edit it, so you can easily
                        integrate it with your product.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="small-12 medium-4 columns">
                <div class="question-item">
                    <h5>Which payment methods do you accept?</h5>
                    <p>You can buy a license with your PayPal account or a credit card.
                        If you wish to send us the money via bank wire transfer, please contact our Sales Team.</p>
                    <h5>How can I get an invoice for my purchase?</h5>
                    <p>The invoice is sent to the email address provided during purchase.
                        Invoices for OEM / Enterprise version and for resellers are, each time,
                        issued manually by our Sales Team.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row read-more"><a href="/faq.html">More questions and answers</a></div>
        </div>
